snippet.textDisplay: We had a dog, nobody knows the age as he was brought to a shelter.  He was part black lab and part something else, that is also unknown. He had bad blood sugar problems. He would constantly fall into a state if confusion, runing into objects until he collapsed and had a seizure where he would make a mess. All we could do is try to stop him from hurting himself while force feeding him corn syrup to raise his blood sugar.   He was like that for a few years. He also had bad fears of abandonment, so when I had to leave, and he was out into a cage, he would always chew through the metal and squeeze through the small hole. Then he would make a mess in the house. We tried to give him a good life, but eventually his failing health did him in. He died at the vet, there was nothing we could do. He passed a few years back. He must have lived a long life, as toward the end his black hair turned grey, and in some spots white. When he was not confused he was fun, smart, fast, and loving.
